//GO
// Go lang is staticaly typed compiled programming langage and it is devoloped by google in 2009...
// is mainly desinged for fast and simple espacially for backend & system level programming...
//  concorancy, simple syntax, simplicity and high performance 

// Concurrency is dealing with multiple tasks at the same time 
// Go achieves concurrency using goroutines.
// Concurrency is about structure, parallelism is about execution.

// Parallism 
// Parallelism is the ability to execute multiple tasks at the exact same time using multiple CPU cores.
//	•	Core 1 → Task A (Video encoding)
//	•	Core 2 → Task B (File download)


//  A GOROUTINES
//  is a lightweight thread managed by the Go runtime that allows functions to run concurrently.
//  Managed by Go scheduler, not the OS and take low memory space
//  goroutine (non-blocking)




